{"title_page": "Bongaigaon Refinery and Petrochemicals", "text_new": "{{moresources|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2018}}\n{{expert needed|date=September 2013|reason=branches/acronyms - see Talk}}\n{{Infobox company \n| name   = IOCL, Bongaigaon Refinery or Erstwhile Bongaigaon Refinery and Petrochemicals Limited \n| logo   = \n| type   = [[Government-owned corporation|State-owned enterprise]] \n|foundation     = 20 February 1974 (Commissioned 1979)\n|location       = [[Bongaigaon]], [[Assam]], [[India]] \n|key_people     =  \n|num_employees  = 1755 (31 March 2005) \n|revenue        =  \n|industry       = [[List of petroleum companies|Oil and gas]]\n|products       = [[Petroleum]]<br />[[Natural gas]]<br />[[Petrochemical]]s\n|homepage       = [http://www.brplindia.com www.brplindia.com]\n}}\n\nThe '''Bongaigaon Refinery & Petrochemicals Ltd.''' ('''BRPL''') now '''[[IOCL]]''', '''[[Bongaigaon Refinery]]''' ('''BGR''') is a [[petroleum refinery]] company in [[India]]. It was incorporated on 20 February 1974 by the government of India.\n\nThe company began with initial funds of Rs. 50 crore (Rs. 500 million), which was increased to Rs. 200 crore by December 1983. The total paid capital of the company was Rs. 199.82 crore as of 31 March 2005.\n\nThe Government of India held the entire paid-up capital of the Company until 1990-91, but sold 25.54% of its shareholding to the public during 1991-92 to 1993-94. The remaining equity of 74.46% was [[divested]] in favor of the Indian Oil Corporation Ltd. on 29 March 2001. As a result, BRPL became a subsidiary company of the Indian Oil Corporation Ltd., a Government owned corporation.{{Citation needed|date=December 2016}}\n\nIn 25 March 2009 BRPL merged with Indian Oil Corporation Limited ([[IOCL]]) to become its eight largest refinery and came to be known as '''[[Bongaigaon Refinery]]''' ('''BGR''').\n\n[[Category:Oil and gas companies of India]]\n[[Category:Bongaigaon]]\n[[Category:Government-owned companies of India]]\n[[Category:Energy in Assam]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Assam]]\n[[Category:Petrochemical companies of India]]\n", "text_old": "{{moresources|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2018}}\n{{expert needed|date=September 2013|reason=branches/acronyms - see Talk}}\n{{Infobox company \n| name   = IOCL, Bongaigaon Refinery or Erstwhile Bongaigaon Refinery and Petrochemicals Limited \n| logo   = \n| type   = [[Government-owned corporation|State-owned enterprise]] \n|foundation     = 20 February 1974 (Commissioned 1979)\n|location       = [[Bongaigaon]], [[Assam]], [[India]] \n|key_people     =  \n|num_employees  = 1755 (31 March 2005) \n|revenue        =  \n|industry       = [[List of petroleum companies|Oil and gas]]\n|products       = [[Petroleum]]<br />[[Natural gas]]<br />[[Petrochemical]]s\n|homepage       = [http://www.brplindia.com www.brplindia.com]\n}}\n\nThe '''Bongaigaon Refinery & Petrochemicals Ltd.''' ('''BRPL''') now '''[[IOCL]]''', '''[[Bongaigaon Refinery]]''' ('''BGR''') is a [[petroleum refinery]] company in [[India]]. It was incorporated on 20 February 1974 by the government of India.\n\nThe company began with initial funds of Rs. 50 crore (Rs. 500 million), which was increased to Rs. 200 crore by December 1983. The total paid capital of the company was Rs. 199.82 crore as of 31 March 2005.\n\nThe Government of India held the entire paid-up capital of the Company until 1990-91, but sold 25.54% of its shareholding to the public during 1991-92 to 1993-94. The remaining equity of 74.46% was [[divested]] in favor of the Indian Oil Corporation Ltd. on 29 March 2001. As a result, BRPL became a subsidiary company of the Indian Oil Corporation Ltd., a Government owned corporation.{{Citation needed|date=December 2016}}\n\nIn 25 March 2009 BRPL merged with Indian Oil Corporation Limited ([[IOCL]]) to become its eight largest refinery and came to be known as '''[[Bongaigaon Refinery]]''' ('''BGR''').\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20131106035603/http://www.brplindia.com/ Bongaigaon Refinery and Petrochemicals Ltd]\n\n[[Category:Oil and gas companies of India]]\n[[Category:Bongaigaon]]\n[[Category:Government-owned companies of India]]\n[[Category:Energy in Assam]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Assam]]\n[[Category:Petrochemical companies of India]]\n", "name_user": "2402:3a80:df5:4f8b:473c:2eb0:d78d:ed14", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(The Government of India held the entire paid-up capital of the Company until 1990-91, but sold 25.54% of its shareholding to the public)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bongaigaon_Refinery_and_Petrochemicals"}
